HEADWORD: Paraselene
<hw>Par`a*se*le"ne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Paraselen⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>para`</grk> beside + <grk>selh`nh</grk> the
moon: cf. F. <ets>paras⟦eacute⟧l⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>A mock moon; an image of the moon which
sometimes appears at the point of intersection of two lunar halos. Cf.
<er>Parhelion</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parashah</ent>⟦br⟧
